266–286 *"From Essentialism to Constructivism? The Gender of Peace and War in Gilman, [[Virginia Woolf|Woolf]], [[Sigmund Freud|Freud]]". ''[[Partial Answers]]: A Journal of Literature and History of Ideas'', January 2004, pp.&nbsp;113–145. *"On the Cusp of Christianity: Virgin Sacrifice in [[Pseudo-Philo]] and [[Amos Oz]]". ''[[The Jewish Quarterly Review]]'', Vol. 97, No. 3, Summer 2007, pp.&nbsp;379–415. *"Deconstructing the Biblical Sources in Israeli Theater: ''Yisurei Iyov'' by [[Hanoch Levin]]". ''[[AJS Review]]'', 1987, 12, pp 251–277<ref>Cambridge Journals Online [http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=4497552 "AJS Review > Volume 12 > Issue 02 > Deconstructing the Biblical Sources in Israeli Theater: Yisurei Iyov by Hanoch Levin"]. Retrieved 2011-03-6</ref> *"The Land of Issac? From 'Glory of Akedah' to 'Issac's Fear'". ''Shma: A Journal of Jewish Ideas'', September 2011, pp.&nbsp;16–17.<ref>{{cite journal|last=S. Feldman|first=Yael|title=The Land of Issac? From 'Glory of Akedah' to 'Issac's Fear|journal=Shma, A Journal of Jewish Ideas| date=September 2011 |url=http://www.shmadigital.com/shma/201109?pg=16|accessdate=19 November 2011}}</ref> *"Nation and Sacrifice: The Akedah and Zionist Ideology", ''Secular Culture and Ideas''.<ref>{{cite web|last=S. Feldman|first=Yael|title=Nation and Sacrifice: The Akedah and Zionist Ideology|url=http://www.secularjewishculture.org/akedah_and_zionism.html|publisher=Center for Cultural Judaism|accessdate=19 November 2011}}</ref> *"On the Cusp of Christianity: Virgin Sacrifice in Pseudo-Philo and Amos Oz." ''JQR'', 97: 3 (Summer 2007): 379-415.
